What are the characteristics that a language should have in order for it to be a good choice to serve as a host for creating internal DSLs? Mention a few languages that meet those expectations.



For a language to be a good choice for creating internal DSLs is that it has to be able to make the language fluent and expressive.
They should have low ceremony, meaning there should be low noise in the language such as unnecessary keywords and symbols.


Languages that are good examples include Groovy, Ruby, and Python. 

